Babajide Sanwo-Olu and Dapo Abiodun, governors of Lagos and Ogun, respectively, were present as the All Progressives Congress (APC) held its presidential campaign in Ogun state on Wednesday. The rally, which held at the MKO Abiola stadium in Abeokuta, also had in attendance hundreds of APC supporters. Bola Tinubu, flag-bearer of the ruling party; Kashim Shettima, his running mate; Olusegun Osoba, former governor of Ogun; and Femi Gbajabiamila, speaker of the house of representatives, were also at the rally. Traditional rulers and clerics were present as well. Below are photos.             